qas.question: Along with the British and Israelis, what forces invaded Egypt in 1956?
What was the combined Israeli-British-French invasion in response to?
Who was the leader of Egypt at the time of the Suez Crisis?
What year saw the publication of Eisenhower's memoirs?

context: In November 1956, Eisenhower forced an end to the combined British, <a0_0>French<a0_0/> and Israeli invasion of Egypt in response to the <a1_0>Suez Crisis<a1_0/>, receiving praise from Egyptian president <a2_0>Gamal Abdel Nasser<a2_0/>. Simultaneously he condemned the brutal <a3_0>Soviet<a3_0/> invasion of Hungary in response to the Hungarian Revolution of 1956. He publicly disavowed his allies at the United Nations, and used financial and diplomatic pressure to make them withdraw from Egypt. Eisenhower explicitly defended his strong position against Britain and France in his memoirs, which were published in <a4_0>1965<a4_0/>.
